sentence: US stock futures eased Tuesday as traders evaluated a weaker-than-expected earnings from Home Depot ( HD ) and looked ahead to a string of readings on the US economy and Federal Reserve Chairman Jerome Powell's semi-annual monetary report to Congress.
Oil prices nudged higher with global benchmark Brent crude up 0.93%, and US West Texas Intermediate crude up 0.3% despite US President Donald Trump's calls to major producers to keep prices steady.

At 8:30 am, data are expected to show a slight increase in housing starts to 1.260 million annualized rate for December from November's 1.256 million rate, while permits are seen easing to 1.290 million for December against November's 1.328 million, according to data compiled by Econoday.
At 9:00 am, the S&P Corelogic Case-Shiller home price index is seen rising 0.4% for December following a 0.3% gain the previous month.
The December reading for the Federal Housing Finance Agency house price index is seen coming in at a 0.4% gain, steady from the prior month's gain.
At 10 am, forecasters see the consumer confidence index coming in at 125.0 for February against January's 120.2 leve.
The Richmond Fed Manufacturing Index is expected to come in at positive 3 for February as compared with January's minus 2.
In equities, shares of Neovasc ( NVCN ) were 28.6% lower pre-bell after the company priced its public offering of common stock at a 28% discount.
